In a statement issued here, the AL General Secretariat expressed "shock and resentment" at the U.S. attack Thursday night on a pharmaceutical plant in Sudan's capital Khartoum, which injured several civilians.
Bashir made the remarks at a news conference held here following an emergency session of the Sudanese National Security and Defense Council to discuss the Thursday bombing of a Sudanese factory by U.S. warplanes.
The 22-member AL accused the U.S. of flagrantly violating international laws and conventions and the United Nations Charter.
